    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1009"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1009">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 703.3212/23.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 29, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>As my friend the Brazilian Ambassador told you yesterday, I am desirous of taking
                    a vacation; but I want to add that I am only willing to do so without
                    embarrassing the Government of the United States and in full and friendly
                    accordance with you in the case that the Department can arrange to intrust
                    American interests to an American and not give them to any other foreign
                    legation here. But on account of the new prospects of an early settlement of
                    things here according to to-day’s news, I suggest that you only study the case
                    for the moment, not taking any steps before hearing from me again.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
